{"parse":{"title":"Kiya Buzurg Ummid","pageid":40007083,"revid":768381758,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 130%;\"><span class=\"fn\">Kiya Buzurg-Ummid</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/wiki/Dawah\" title=\"Dawah\">D\u0101\u02bf\u012b</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nUnknown</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n1138</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Ethnicity\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ethnicity\">Ethnicity</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Dailamite\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dailamite\">Dailamite</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\nIran</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Religion</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\">Islam</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Jurisprudence</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Isma%27ilism\" title=\"Isma&#39;ilism\">Nizari Ismaili Shi'ism</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Main interest(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Kalam\" title=\"Kalam\">Islamic theology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Fiqh\" title=\"Fiqh\">Islamic jurisprudence</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Notable idea(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Evolution\" title=\"Evolution\">Evolution</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Tawhid\" title=\"Tawhid\">Oneness of God</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none; padding:0;\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size: 105%; background: transparent; text-align: left;\">Influenced&#160;by</div>\n<ul class=\"NavContent\" style=\"list-style: none none; margin-left: 0; text-align:center; font-size: 105%; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: inherit;\"><li style=\"line-height: inherit; margin: 0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Hassan-i_Sabbah\" title=\"Hassan-i Sabbah\">Hassan-i Sabbah</a></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none; padding:0;\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size: 105%; background: transparent; text-align: left;\">Influenced</div>\n<ul class=\"NavContent\" style=\"list-style: none none; margin-left: 0; text-align:center; font-size: 105%; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: inherit;\"><li style=\"line-height: inherit; margin: 0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Muhammad_ibn_Kiya_Buzurg_Ummid\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Muhammad ibn Kiya Buzurg Ummid\">Muhammad ibn Kiya Buzurg Ummid</a></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Kiy\u0101 Buzurg-Umm\u012bd</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Persian_language\" title=\"Persian language\">Persian</a>: <span lang=\"fa\" dir=\"rtl\">\u06a9\u06cc\u0627 \u0628\u0632\u0631\u06af \u0627\u0645\u06cc\u062f</span>&#8206;) (died 1138) was a <i><a href=\"/wiki/Dawah\" title=\"Dawah\">d\u0101\u02bf\u012b</a></i> and the second <a href=\"/wiki/Nizari_Ismaili_state\" title=\"Nizari Ismaili state\">Nizari Isma'ili</a> ruler of <a href=\"/wiki/Alamut_Castle\" title=\"Alamut Castle\">Alamut Castle</a> from 1124 to 1138 <a href=\"/wiki/Common_Era\" title=\"Common Era\">CE</a> (or 518\u2014532 <a href=\"/wiki/Hijri_year\" title=\"Hijri year\">AH</a>). He was of <a href=\"/wiki/Dailamite\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dailamite\">Daylami</a> origin<sup id=\"cite_ref-iranicaonline.org_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-iranicaonline.org-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> from the region of <a href=\"/wiki/Rudbar\" title=\"Rudbar\">Rudbar</a>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:237px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lambesar_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/59/Lambesar_2.jpg/235px-Lambesar_2.jpg\" width=\"235\" height=\"166\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/59/Lambesar_2.jpg/353px-Lambesar_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/59/Lambesar_2.jpg/470px-Lambesar_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1470\" data-file-height=\"1040\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lambesar_2.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Kiya Buzurg captured the <a href=\"/wiki/Lambsar_Castle\" title=\"Lambsar Castle\">Lambsar Castle</a> from Rasamuj and rebuilt it into a major stronghold using local labour. He was appointed by <a href=\"/wiki/Hasan_Sabbah\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hasan Sabbah\">Hasan Sabbah</a> (d. 1124) as its governor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks collapsible\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%\"><tbody><tr><th style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;font-size:88%; line-height:200%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Basmala.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Bismillahir Rahmanir Rahim\"><img alt=\"Bismillahir Rahmanir Rahim\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Basmala.svg/200px-Basmala.svg.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Basmala.svg/300px-Basmala.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Basmala.svg/400px-Basmala.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"608\" data-file-height=\"119\" /></a> <span style=\"font-size:115%;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Part of <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Shia_Islam\" title=\"Category:Shia Islam\">a series</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Shia_Islam\" title=\"Shia Islam\">Sh\u012ba Islam</a></span></span> \n<br /><span style=\"font-size:200%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Isma%27ilism\" title=\"Isma&#39;ilism\">Isma\u2018ilism</a></span></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.2em 0 0.4em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Ismail lion calligram\"><img alt=\"Ismail lion calligram\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg/200px-Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"163\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg/300px-Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg/400px-Shiite_Calligraphy_symbolising_Ali_as_Tiger_of_God.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"503\" data-file-height=\"409\" /></a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left\"><a href=\"/wiki/Imamah_(Ismaili_doctrine)\" title=\"Imamah (Ismaili doctrine)\">Concepts</a></div><div class=\"NavContent hlist\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Esoteric_interpretation_of_the_Quran\" title=\"Esoteric interpretation of the Quran\">Qur'an</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Zahir_(Islam)\" title=\"Zahir (Islam)\">\u1e92\u0101hir</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Batin_(Islam)\" title=\"Batin (Islam)\">B\u0101tin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/N%C5%ABr_(Islam)\" title=\"N\u016br (Islam)\">N\u016br</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Pir_(Sufism)\" title=\"Pir (Sufism)\">P\u012br</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ginans\" title=\"Ginans\">Ginans</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/%27Aql\" title=\"&#39;Aql\">'Aql</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ilm_(Arabic)\" title=\"Ilm (Arabic)\">\u02bfIlm</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hujja\" title=\"Hujja\">Hujja</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Da%27i_al-Mutlaq\" title=\"Da&#39;i al-Mutlaq\">D\u0101'\u012b</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Dawah\" title=\"D